"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-mystery-man-goes-viral-after-dive-into-pool-to-retrieve-lost-cap-at-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  A lifeguard was called upon to retrieve American swimmer Emma Weber's swim cap after her 100m breaststroke heat.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.9999999999456577, \"rank\": 5.434219610928653e-11, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703097123, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998166600644196, \"rank\": 0.00015589304274022533, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.995803209144431, \"rank\": 0.0035281693390894066, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"score\": 0.9684477124595607, \"rank\": 0.0318062077609032, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: AFP  PublishedJul 30, 2024, 11:45 AM  UpdatedJul 30, 2024, 02:48 PM  PARIS - Whistles and catcalls rang out at La Defense Arena between races in the women's 100m breaststroke heats when a middle-aged man in multi-coloured swimming trunks made his way to the pool, but seconds later he went on to become the toast of the Games.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American swimmer Emma Weber had lost her cap in the fourth heat on July 28 and before the fifth heat got underway, a lifeguard was called upon to retrieve the cap from the bottom of the pool.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998166600644196, \"rank\": 0.00015589304274022533, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.995803209144431, \"rank\": 0.0035281693390894066, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"score\": 0.9684477124595607, \"rank\": 0.0318062077609032, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Weber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At first, the confused crowd in the 15,000-seat arena did not understand what was going on but when the lifeguard dove into the water and retrieved the white cap, they quickly realised what was happening and gave him a loud cheer.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On his part, the lifeguard seized his Olympic moment and as he climbed out of the pool, he gave the fans a quick wave before adjusting his trunks and walking off.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This situation is common at swimming competitions,\\\" a Games spokesperson was quoted as saying by CNN.\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.999999993732672, \"rank\": 6.2657424085640915e-09, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As the lifeguards are the only people wearing swimwear, apart from the athletes, a request may be made to fetch an item at the bottom of the pool prior to the next race.\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In this case, the request was made to the lifeguard closest to the item.\\\"\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The spokesperson added that the lifeguard did not want to be named but American broadcaster NBC gave him the moniker \\\"Bob the cap catcher\\\" and it has stuck ever since he went viral on social media.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998166600644196, \"rank\": 0.00015589304274022533, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.8163328502927799, \"rank\": 0.2245794831092694, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"score\": 0.8844385885787912, \"rank\": 0.09937755263017319, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Dalton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Olympics 2024  Olympics  Swimming  Sports and recreation  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 1926, \"end\": 1934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": []}]}"